    <who name="Cole Robinson">crobinso</who>
    <bug_when>2016-06-01 19:59:06 -0400</bug_when>
    <thetext>Not sure if this is virgl, kernel, qemu, spice, or something else...

Update to date f24 host and guest, configured with spice gl. Run supertuxkart in the VM. If selecting &apos;story mode&apos; the game becomes unresponsive on the &apos;loading&apos; screen. If selecting &apos;single player&apos; the game becomes unresponsive on the character select screen, presumably trying to render the character vehicle previews. Note the music is still playing this whole time so it doesn&apos;t seem that the game completely locks, there just isn&apos;t any way to interact with it anymore.

100% reproducible for me. No relevant stderr messages in the libvirt qemu log file. Switching the video card to &apos;qxl&apos; and rebooting the VM makes supertuxkart work, albeit with an opengl warning and choppy graphics.</thetext>
